{"title":"Specialized EXOS EVO XC Shoes bring light weight Dyneema tech to S-Works MTB","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/08/specialized-exos-evo-xc-shoes-bring-light-weight-dyneema-tech-to-s-works-mtb/","date":1623168029000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Remember those <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/02/26/specialized-exos-99g-road-bike-shoes-are-unlike-anything-youve-ever-seen/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">insane 99g Specialized EXOS 99 road shoes</a>? They were joined by a more ‘reasonable’ 150g standard EXOS version, but both models relied on a custom made Dyneema upper which provided the necessary support without any stretch. It also allowed the shoes to be constructed to reach their outrageous weights (among other clever weight saving efforts).</p><p>Of course, Specialized has been hard at work bringing that same tech over to the MTB side. The new S-Works EXOS EVO does just that.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb13/ng:webp/ngcb13\" alt=\"Specialized EXOS EVO XC Shoes \" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb13/ng:webp/ngcb13\" ezoid=\"0.8019660415637653\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112445/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-6-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 630w\"></a></p><p>Similar to road racing shoes, XC MTB shoes for racing at the highest level need to be efficient. Being super light doesn’t hurt either. Calling it the lightest shoe they’ve ever created, the EXOS EVO checks in at just 231g.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized EXOS EVO XC Shoes from top of BOA\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112146/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoe-studio-shots-1-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>To get there, the EXOS EVO takes many cues from the EXOS with a proprietary Dyneema bonded upper that resists stretching and weighs less than previous S-Works uppers. A centrally mounted BOA Li2 dial is used to offer better micro-adjustment and fit. Specialized says that they also uses a “reimagined toe box, which uses a sleeve that stretches comfortably over the top of the toes and forefoot while maintaining room for movement and flexion.”</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized EXOS EVO XC Shoes heel cup\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112501/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-2-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Instead of a traditional thermoplastic heel cup, the EXOS line uses Dyneema Cubic Tech and a layered design to make a heel cup that is just as vertically rigid, but supposedly molds better to the foot for improved fit. It’s also lighter. As Specialized’s footwear category manager, Stephen Quay, told us from the EXOS launch, Cubic Tech is a special blend of Dyneema fibers that can be oriented in specific directions to prevent stretch in all directions.</p><p>The technology is also used on parachutes for spacecraft and spinnaker sales for racing sailboats, so it can hold up to even the world’s strongest sprinters.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-4\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112507/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07112507/Specialized-Exos-Evo-mountain-bike-shoex-world-cup-XC-3.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized EXOS EVO XC Shoes sole\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/upload